data.title: Björk
data.meta_description: Read all about Björk with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Released her eponymous debut album at the age of 11; her mother provided the artwork

Studied piano, flute and voice at the Barnamusikskoli Reykjavikur in Reykjavik for 10 years

First found success with her band the Sugarcubes in the late 1980s

Made her acting debut in the 1990 film The Juniper Tree

Won the Cannes Film Festival Best Actress award for her performance in the 2000 musical Dancer in the Dark; she also contributed music

Received France's National Order of Merit in 2001

Performed her song "Oceania" at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, Greece

Awards

2001Golden Globe-Best Original Song - Motion Picture: nominated

2001Golden Globe-Best Performance by an Actress in a Motion Picture - Drama: nominated

2001Bodil Awards-Best Actress in a Leading Role: winner

2001Robert Awards-Best Actress in a Leading Role: winner

2000Cannes Film Festival-Best Actress: winner

2000Oscar-Best Achievement in Music (Original Song): nominated

2000European Film Academy-Best European Actress: winner

2000Jameson People's Choice Award-Best European Actress: winner

2000National Board of Review-Best Musical Performance: winner

2000European Film Awards-European Actress: winner
